Program: Outlook
Title: 24/10/2011
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p00kv55d
Last Broadcast Date: Tue 25 Oct 2011
Extraordinary personal stories from around the world. Today, Mohamed Al-Murabit, the Libyan doctor who treated rebel fighters who were being refused care in hospitals taken over by Colonel Gaddafi's troops. Now he wants to set up a political party. Plus, a Sierra Leonean teacher who fled Libya during the battle to oust Colonel Gaddafi. Also, a Japanese woman who defied her family's wishes to help tsunami victims. And, the British grandmother who survived her own 'James Bond moment'. Show less